html?thread=21560873#t21560873","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21560873#t21560873","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21560873#t21560873","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"grrm","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":21560873,"talkid":84222,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21560873#t21560873","above":21560105,"upictitle":"George R.R. Martin: Spain","article":"I would love that, but the hard part is getting King to sign on.  He used to do a lot of stuff for original anthologies, but I think he got overwhelmed by the sheer number of invitations.  A Stephen King story in any anthology produces a sharp spike in sales.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"April 30 2015, 19:41:09 UTC","parent":21560105,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Stephen King","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"grrm","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"grrm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"grrm","ctime_ts":1430422869,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/121545515/65624740","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21567785#t21567785","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21567785#t21567785","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21567785#t21567785","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_2088910","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://www.facebook.com/piet.nel.771","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":21567785,"talkid":84249,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21567785#t21567785","above":21560873,"upictitle":"Piet Nel: pic#121545515","article":"This is one of the reasons why I've stuck with Stephen King, even though I don't like all his books. He is one of the few mega-sellers who still write short fiction, and because I love anthologies and collections, that keeps him on my bookshelf.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"May 1 2015, 07:37:40 UTC","parent":21560873,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Stephen King","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://www.facebook.com/piet.nel.771","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Piet Nel","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_2088910","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=65624740&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Piet Nel","ctime_ts":1430465860,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/124911681/75491528","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21561897#t21561897","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21561897#t21561897","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21561897#t21561897","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"mordreddayne","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://mordreddayne.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":21561897,"talkid":84226,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21561897#t21561897","upictitle":"Chris Walker: pic#124911681","article":"The Eyes of The Dragon was the first fantasy book I remember reading. My father read The Hobbit to me, but this is the first one that was all mine. I stayed up way past bedtime reading it, hoping my parents wouldn't notice the light creeping out from under my door. It's a simple story in a lot of ways, but it does play around with some fantasy tropes, most notably the \"everyone lives happily ever after\" idea. Plus, it features an iteration of Flagg, one of King's best characters. There are a number of EotD references throughout the Dark Tower series. Aside from the Flagg connection, Dennis and Thomas are mentioned, as well as Delain and Garlan.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"April 30 2015, 20:56:26 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"The Eyes of The Dragon","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://mordreddayne.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"mordreddayne","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"mordreddayne","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://mordreddayne.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"mordreddayne","ctime_ts":1430427386,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/124812397/75134242","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21562409#t21562409","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21562409#t21562409","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21562409#t21562409","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"brgibbons","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://brgibbons.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":21562409,"talkid":84228,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21562409#t21562409","upictitle":"Brian Gibbons: pic#124812397","article":"Note that King did receive the <a href=\"http://www.sfadb.com/World_Fantasy_Awards_2004\" rel=\"nofollow\">2004 World Fantasy Award for Lifetime Achievement</a>, so he hasn't been completely overlooked there.<br /><br />His <i>11/22/63</i> did receive a number of nominations for the <a href=\"http://www.thehugoawards.org/content/pdf/2012HugoVotingReport.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">2012 Hugo Award for Best Novel</a>, but didn't come anywhere close making it to the final ballot.<br /><br />But, sure, horror, like paranormal romance, generally falls into that \"Well, technically, it's SF but I really don't think of it that way\" category for a lot of people.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"April 30 2015, 21:47:39 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"World Fantasy Award","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://brgibbons.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"brgibbons","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"brgibbons","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://brgibbons.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"brgibbons","ctime_ts":1430430459,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/121313083/9947615","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21563689#t21563689","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21563689#t21563689","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21563689#t21563689","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"douglascohen","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://douglascohen.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":21563689,"talkid":84233,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21563689#t21563689","upictitle":"Douglas Cohen: pic#121313083","article":"As coincidence would have it, I just finished reading the Flynn story yesterday.  A very entertaining read.  Glad to see she won the award.  ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"April 30 2015, 22:21:07 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://douglascohen.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"douglascohen","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"douglascohen","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://douglascohen.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"douglascohen","ctime_ts":1430432467,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/124344032/73526708","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21565993#t21565993","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21565993#t21565993","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21565993#t21565993","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_2918109","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://www.facebook.com/brooklyn.ann.7","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":21565993,"talkid":84242,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/425001.html?thread=21565993#t21565993","upictitle":"Brooklyn Ann: pic#124344032","article":"^ As a previous commenter pointed out, King did win a Hugo and a Locus in the Non-Fiction Category for DANSE MACABRE (Which I thought was fantastic) as well as a Locus for ON WRITING. (Which is my bible). <br /><br />...although it still blows my mind that his incredible FICTION never won either of the above. Especially the titles you mentioned! Not even The Talisman ?!! <br />And I can't believe he never won an Edgar before! (Dolores Claiborne, Rose Madder, or Gerald's Game, anyone?) I find it odd that he is often so underrated for his popularity when so many others are overrated for theirs. <br /><br />Stephen King is one of my biggest heroes and inspirations and I was happy to hear his good news first on your blog!    ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"May 1 2015, 02:23:37 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Hail to the King!!! and King&#39;s Hugo...","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://www.facebook.com/brooklyn.ann.7","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Brooklyn Ann","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_2918109","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=73526708&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Brooklyn Ann","ctime_ts":1430447017,"tracked":0}]}